  "prompt": "Who was the first teacher in the world?",
  "response": "Determining the \"first teacher in the world\" is challenging due to the lack of historical records from ancient times. Education and teaching have been integral to human societies since prehistory, with knowledge passed down orally from generation to generation. \n\nIn many cultures, early teachers were likely tribal elders, shamans, or parents who taught survival skills, traditions, and moral values. As civilizations developed, formalized roles for teachers emerged. For example:\n\n- **Ancient Mesopotamia** is often credited with having some of the earliest formal schools, where scribes taught writing and record-keeping.\n- **Confucius (551\u2013479 BCE)** in China is one of the most famous early educators, emphasizing morality, social relationships, and justice.\n- **Socrates (470\u2013399 BCE)** in ancient Greece is considered one of the foundational figures in Western philosophy and teaching.\n\nWhile it's impossible to identify the very first teacher, these figures represent key milestones in the evolution of teaching as a profession and practice.",
